                        <ul class="list-group">
                            <li class="list-group-item py-2">
                                1. The app is designed to use % correction values recommended by Chang et al. to determine if the PT or PTT corrects, as noted in this figure:
                                <img class="img img-fluid py-2" src="/img/clin-path/Chang_PT_correction_table.png">
                                2. A value >= 40% at 4:1 mix and immediate clotting time correction has the highest specificity for factor deficiency

                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item py-2">
                                3. For the PTT, a value >= 50% at immediate 4:1 mix or >=10% at incubated 4:1 mix has the highest specificity for factor deficiency
                                <img class="img img-fluid py-2" src="/img/clin-path/Chang_PTT_correction_table.png">
                                4. The incubated 4:1 mix cutoff of >=10% has a slightly better sensitivity and specificity and will drive interpretations
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item py-2">
                                5. The various permutations of PTT Chang corrections can be summarized as below:
                                <img class="img img-fluid py-2" src="/img/clin-path/Chang_PTT_summary_table.png">
                            </li>
